  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best digital marketing course online for a beginner?",
  "response": "There are several highly regarded online digital marketing courses for beginners. Here are a few of the best options:\n\n1. **Google Digital Garage**:\n   - **Course**: Fundamentals of Digital Marketing\n   - **Provider**: Google\n   - **Overview**: This free course covers essential digital marketing concepts, including SEO, SEM, social media, and analytics. It includes practical exercises and is certified by Google.\n\n2. **HubSpot Academy**:\n   - **Course**: Digital Marketing Certification\n   - **Overview**: HubSpot offers a free digital marketing course that covers inbound marketing, content marketing, email marketing, and social media marketing. It\u2019s well-structured and offers a certification upon completion.\n\n3. **Coursera**:\n   - **Course**: Digital Marketing Specialization\n   - **Provider**: University of Illinois\n   - **Overview**: This is a more comprehensive series of courses, covering digital marketing analytics, search engine optimization, social media marketing, and more. While it is not free, you can access it for free with financial aid or during a free trial.\n\n4. **edX**:\n   - **Course**: Digital Marketing MicroMasters\n   - **Provider**: Cornell University\n   - **Overview**: This MicroMasters program offers a deeper dive into digital marketing strategies. It includes several courses and is a paid option, but it provides high-quality content and certification.\n\n5. **LinkedIn Learning**:\n   - **Course**: Online Marketing Foundations\n   - **Overview**: This course introduces the basics of digital marketing across various channels and is accessible to those with a LinkedIn Learning subscription. It\u2019s beginner-friendly and offers a certificate upon completion.\n\n6. **Udemy**:\n   - **Course**: The Complete Digital Marketing Course\n   - **Overview**: A very popular option on Udemy, this course covers various aspects of digital marketing, including SEO, Facebook ads, Google Analytics, and email marketing. Udemy frequently has discounts, making it affordable.\n\nBefore choosing a course, consider your learning style, the depth of information you're looking for, and whether you prefer a free course or are willing to invest in a more comprehensive program.",
